Mohamed Soltan, 27, was sentenced to life in prison for plotting unrest in Egypt in July 2013 . 
  He and 36 others were found guilty of plotting unrest against the military-backed government . 
  Muslim Brotherhood leader Mohamed Badie and 13 others were ordered to be executed . 
  Soltan moved to Egypt in 2012 to be near his mother who was undergoing cancer treatment . 
  He has been on a hunger strike and his father was a member of the Muslim Brotherhood . 
 